      "id": "LN_01",
      "section": "learn",
      "difficulty": 0,
      "type": "concept_card",
      "title": "×8 Facts",
      "content": "8×1=8, 8×2=16, 8×3=24, 8×4=32, 8×5=40, 8×6=48, 8×7=56, 8×8=64, 8×9=72, 8×10=80.",
      "cpa_phase": "concrete",
      "visual_type": "none"
    },
    {
      "id": "LN_02",
      "section": "learn",
      "difficulty": 0,
      "type": "concept_card",
      "title": "Strategy: Double the ×4 Fact",
      "content": "Since 8 = 2 × 4, every ×8 fact is just double the ×4 fact. 8 × 6 = (4 × 6) × 2 = 24 × 2 = 48.",
      "cpa_phase": "concrete",
      "visual_type": "none"
    },
    {
      "id": "LN_03",
      "section": "learn",
      "difficulty": 0,
      "type": "concept_card",
      "title": "Strategy: Double-Double-Double",
      "content": "Since 8 = 2 × 2 × 2, you can double three times. 8 × 7: double 7 → 14, double 14 → 28, double 28 → 56.",
      "cpa_phase": "pictorial",
      "visual_type": "none"
    },
    {
      "id": "LN_04",
      "section": "learn",
      "difficulty": 0,
      "type": "concept_card",
      "title": "Strategy: Break 8 into 5 + 3",
      "content": "Use the Distributive Property: 8 × 7 = (5 × 7) + (3 × 7) = 35 + 21 = 56. Pick whichever split you remember best.",
      "cpa_phase": "pictorial",
      "visual_type": "none"
    },
